description: A 15-year-old has been questioned following a reported incident in Cleethorpes on Sunday.
title: Teenager arrested on suspicion of Cleethorpes railway bridge rape
title_page: Teenager arrested on suspicion of Cleethorpes railway bridge rape - BBC News
maintext:
A 15-year-old boy has been arrested on suspicion of rape following an incident in Cleethorpes, Humberside Police said.
The force received a call on Sunday after a woman reported she was attacked by someone walking a dog on a railway footbridge near Harrington Street at about 21:40 GMT.
The teenager was taken into custody on Thursday and has been released on conditional bail while investigations continue.
Humberside Police said it would like to speak to anyone with information, CCTV or dashcam footage from the area.
